text: Edna May Davey (24 July 1909 – 2000), later Hamilton, was an Australian swimmer. She competed in two events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1909 births Category:2000 deaths Category:Australian female swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Australia Category:Swimmers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from London
